The Fountain University, Osogbo, Osun State has got an approval from the National Universities Commission (NUC) to begin Nursing Science, Environmental Health Science, Law, Medical Laboratory Science and Public Health programmes with effect from 2020/2021 Academic Session. A statement by the Public Relations Officer of the institution, Mr Toyeeb Olayinka, said the Director of Academic Planning, Dr N. B. Saliu, in a letter conveyed the approval on behalf of the NUC Executive Secretary. “Dr Saliu congratulated the university for the accomplishment, saying that the NUC panel of experts were satisfied with the human and material resources made available for the commencement of the programmes during the resource verification visit. “The Vice Chancellor, Prof. Amidu Sanni, hailed the proprietor, staff and stakeholders of the university for putting all hands-on deck at ensuring the successful commencement of the programmes.”  